I&#39;m using Moodle 3.5.2 and PHP 7.0(with the required extensions) to run an e-learning site, the client wanted to add a personality test so i found a Questionnaire plugin that can do that and then install it.

So i tested the plugin by creating a new Questionnaire that can have a feedback (the closest you can get to a personality test in Moodle). However when i clicked the submit button no data is being passed through. Through inspecting the html apparently the form ended too soon and the control buttons aren&#39;t counted as part of the form and that&#39;s why it&#39;s not passing any data(duh)

Here&#39;s the mustache responsible for all this

```
&lt;div class=&quot;mod_questionnaire_completepage generalbox&quot;&gt;
    {{#notifications}}{{{.}}}{{/notifications}}
    {{{respondentinfo}}}
    {{#title}}&lt;h3 class=&quot;surveyTitle&quot;&gt;{{.}}&lt;/h3&gt;{{/title}}{{{printblank}}}
    {{#subtitle}}&lt;h4 class=&quot;surveySubTitle&quot;&gt;{{.}}&lt;/h4&gt;{{/subtitle}}
    {{#addinfo}}&lt;div class=&quot;addInfo&quot;&gt;{{{.}}}&lt;/div&gt;{{/addinfo}}
    {{#message}}&lt;div class=&quot;message&quot;&gt;{{{.}}}&lt;/div&gt;{{/message}}
    &lt;div class=&quot;generalbox&quot;&gt;
        {{{formstart}}}
        {{#questions}}{{{.}}}{{/questions}}
        {{#pageinfo}}{{{.}}}{{/pageinfo}}
        &lt;div class=&quot;notice&quot; style=&quot;padding: 0.5em 0 0.5em 0.2em;&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;buttons&quot;&gt;
                {{{controlbuttons}}}
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        {{{formend}}}
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
```

here&#39;s the php class for the control buttons
```
$formdatareferer = !empty($formdata-&gt;referer) ? htmlspecialchars($formdata-&gt;referer) : &#39;&#39;;
